<subSubSection id="C3346BEBBF56FF8DE2E8E280FED4FF41" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B913860BF56FF8DE2E8E280FED4FF41" blockId="14.[151,1436,1590,2013]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B95AE472BF56FF8CE2E8E280FEE2F82D" bold="true" box="[199,317,1951,1977]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks:</emphasis>
The number of specimens from the lot 
<accessionNumber id="947DA583BF56FF8CE0D5E280FCA0F82D" box="[762,895,1950,1977]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/NUP15614" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">NUP 15614</accessionNumber>
was incorrectly cited as 10 (
<specimenCount id="9D28F3E9BF56FF8CE6EDE280FAC4F82D" box="[1218,1307,1951,1977]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="male">3 males</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount id="9D28F3E9BF56FF8CE708E280FA4AF82E" box="[1319,1429,1951,1978]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="female">7 females</specimenCount>
) in the original description, and the locality was incorrectly stated as being from Engenheiro Beltrão, rio Mourão, rio Ivaí basin, upper rio 
<collectingRegion id="49EAF682BF57FF8DE351E588FE15FF25" box="[382,458,151,177]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Paraná</collectingRegion>
basin. Valid as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E43E3BF57FF8DE057E588FAD4FF25" authority="(Roxo, Zawadzki &amp; Troy, 2014)" baseAuthorityName="Roxo, Zawadzki &amp; Troy" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[632,1291,151,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Curculionichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oliveirai">
<emphasis id="B95AE472BF57FF8DE057E588FC42FF25" box="[632,925,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Curculionichthys oliveirai</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF4591BF57FF8DE183E588FADCFF25" author="Roxo, F. F. &amp; Zawadzki, C. H. &amp; Troy, W. P." box="[940,1283,151,177]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="57 - 78" refId="ref37640" refString="Roxo, F. F., Zawadzki, C. H. &amp; Troy, W. P. (2014) Description of two new species of Hisonotus Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann, 1889 (Ostariophysi, Loricariidae) from the rio Parana-Paraguay basin, Brazil. ZooKeys, 395, 57 - 78. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 395.6910" type="journal article" year="2014">Roxo, Zawadzki &amp; Troy, 2014</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF4591BF57FF8DE76AE588FF20FF41" author="Roxo, F. F. &amp; Silva, G. S. C. &amp; Ochoa, L. E. &amp; Oliveira, C." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="103" refId="ref37208" refString="Roxo, F. F., Silva, G. S. C., Ochoa, L. E. &amp; Oliveira, C. (2015) Description of a new genus and three new species of Otothyrinae (Siluriformes, Loricariidae). ZooKeys, (534), 103. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 534.6169" type="journal article" year="2015">
Roxo 
<emphasis id="B95AE472BF57FF8DE7A7E588FF72FF41" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al</emphasis>
., 2015
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
